To create an if/then statement in C, you need to use the if-else statement, which allows you to execute a block of code if a certain condition is met and specify an alternative block of code to be executed if the condition is not met. Here's an example:

if (condition) {
  // Code to be executed if the condition is true
} else {
  // Code to be executed if the condition is false
}

In this example, the if statement checks if the condition is true, and if it is, the code inside the if block is executed. If the condition is false, the code inside the else block is executed.
